Brussels stabbing: Multiple people have been stabbed outside the Turkish Consulate
STABBING: Reports suggest three Kurds were attacked by supporters of Turkish President Erdoğan
Several people have been wounded outside the Turkish Consulate in the Belgian city.
Police were called to the scene at about 5pm.
One of the three victims was slashed in the stomach and is in a serious condition.
Turkish people were standing outside waiting to vote in the Turkish constitutional referendum, LaLibre.be reported.